/wiki/Luis_Rivera_(athlete): Luis Alberto Rivera Morales (born 21 June 1987, in Agua Prieta) is a Mexican long jumper. His personal best is 8.46 metres, achieved in July 2013.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2013_Summer_Unive: Athletics was contested at the 2013 Summer Universiade from July 7 to 12 at the Universiade Village Stadium and the Central Stadium in Kazan, Russia.
The men's long jump event at the 2013 Summer Universiade was held on 11–12 July.
/wiki/Patrick_Loliger: Patrick Alexandre Ernst Loliger Salas (born June 20, 1985) is a Mexican rower who has made a name for himself around the globe due to his various participations in rowing competitions such as the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics, and most recently in the 012 London Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Rowing_at_the_2013_Summer_Universi: Rowing was contested at the 2013 Summer Universiade from July 6 to 8 at the Rowing Centre in Kazan, Russia.
The men's single sculls competition at the 2013 Summer Universiade in Kazan took place the Kazan Rowing Centre.
/wiki/Daniel_Corral: Daniel Corral Barrón (born 25 January 1990 in Ensenada) is a Mexican gymnast.
/wiki/Gymnastics_at_the_2013_Summer_Univ: Gymnastics was contested at the 2013 Summer Universiade from July 7 to 10 at the Gymnastics Centre in Kazan, Russia. Artistic and rhythmic gymnastics was the two disciplines of gymnastics contested.
/wiki/Elsa_Garc\u00eda: Elsa García Rodriguez (born February 8, 1990) is a Mexican artistic gymnast and she competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Gymnastics_at_the_2013_Summer_Univ: The women's floor gymnastics competition at the 2013 Summer Universiade was held on July 10 at the Gymnastics Centre in Kazan.
/wiki/Football_at_the_2013_Summer_Univer: Football was contested at the 2013 Summer Universiade from July 5 to 16 in Kazan, Russia.
The women's tournament of football at the 2013 Summer Universiade was held from 5 to 16 July in Kazan, Russia.
/wiki/Arantxa_Ch\u00e1vez: Arantxa Elizabeth Chávez Muñoz (born 30 January 1991 in Mexico City, Mexico) is a Mexican diver. In 2012, she achieved qualification to participate at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the individual 3 metre trampoline event. At the Olympics, she failed to reach the semifinal and was classified 29th.
/wiki/Diving_at_the_2013_Summer_Universi: Diving was contested at the 2013 Summer Universiade from July 5 to 12 at the Aquatics Palace in Kazan, Russia.
/wiki/Yahel_Castillo: Yahel Ernesto Castillo Huerta (born June 6 1987) is a Mexican diver.
/wiki/Daniel_Islas_(diver): Alejandro Daniel Islas Arroyo (born 24 May 1992 in Mexico State, Mexico) is a Mexican diver. In 2012 he achieved qualification to participate at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the individual 3 metre trampoline event.
/wiki/Iv\u00e1n_Garc\u00eda_(diver): Iván Alejandro García Navarro (born 25 October 1993) is a Mexican diver. He is nicknamed "Pollo" ("Chicken"). He competes in diving and represented Mexico at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London.He won a silver medal in the 10m Synchronized Platform with his partner Germán Sánchez with a high score of 468.90. In the individual 10m Platform, García came the 7th with a score of 521.65.
/wiki/Germ\u00e1n_S\u00e1nchez_(diver): Germán Saúl Sánchez Sánchez (born 24 June 1992) is a Mexican diver. He is nicknamed "Duva". At the age of 16, he competed in the Men's individual 10m platform at the 2008 Summer Olympics and came in 22nd. He won one gold medal in the 2011 Pan-American Games. At the 2012 Summer Olympics in London, he won a silver medal in the synchronized 10m platform with his partner Iván García. In the individual 10m platform, Sánchez came 14th. In 2016, Sánchez took part in his third Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, where he came 5th in the synchronized 10m platform, again alongside Iván García. Twelve days later, Sánchez won the silver medal in individual 10m platform. and 9th in the semi-final. He became the third Mexican athlete to win an Olympic silver medal in Men's individual 10m platform after Joaquín Capilla (1952) and Álvaro Gaxiola (1968). He is also the only Mexican diver who has won Olympic medals in both individual and synchronized events.
/wiki/Paola_Espinosa: Paola Milagros Espinosa Sánchez (born 31 July 1985) is a Mexican diver and represented Mexico at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, where she was her national team's flagbearer, and the 2012 Summer Olympics in London.
/wiki/Rommel_Pacheco: Rommel Agmed Pacheco Manrufo (born 12 July 1986) is a Mexican diver. He was the gold medalist in the 10-meter platform at the 2003 Pan American Games. In the 2004 Summer Olympics he finished in 10th place in the 10-meter platform and 3-meter springboard. In the 2008 Summer Olympics he finished in 8th place in the 10-meter platform.
/wiki/Mexico_at_the_2013_Summer_Universi: Mexico competed at the 2013 Summer Universiade in Kazan, Russia from 6 to 17 July 2013.
